1
00:00:10,838 --> 00:00:12,905
READY OR NOT: TEXAS

2
00:00:13,471 --> 00:00:16,805
DAY 3 MORNING
FINALLY ARRIVED IN DALLAS

3
00:00:19,671 --> 00:00:23,538
Why does Seo-jin visit Dallas so often?

4
00:00:23,605 --> 00:00:25,038
They have Smoothie King.

5
00:00:25,105 --> 00:00:27,138
What is that?

6
00:00:27,205 --> 00:00:29,171
HERE'S THE STORY

7
00:00:32,405 --> 00:00:34,771
When we get to Dallas…

8
00:00:34,838 --> 00:00:35,938
IN DALLAS…

9
00:00:36,005 --> 00:00:38,038
…we can meet
Korea's most successful businessman.

10
00:00:38,105 --> 00:00:39,971
You know him personally, right?

11
00:00:40,038 --> 00:00:41,271
NODS

12
00:00:41,338 --> 00:00:43,138
He's the CEO of Smoothie King.

13
00:00:43,205 --> 00:00:44,871
SEO-JIN'S ACQUAINTANCE
CEO OF SMOOTHIE KING

14
00:00:44,938 --> 00:00:46,538
- The CEO of Smoothie King?
- Yes.

15
00:00:46,605 --> 00:00:48,571
- Is he younger than you?
- He is.

16
00:00:48,638 --> 00:00:49,805
SEO-JIN'S 30-YEAR-LONG FRIEND

17
00:00:49,871 --> 00:00:51,105
I've never had it before.

18
00:00:51,171 --> 00:00:52,471
What is it?

19
00:00:52,538 --> 00:00:54,171
- Is it like a slushie?
- It is.

20
00:00:54,238 --> 00:00:55,805
- It's made of fruit.
- It's healthy.

21
00:00:55,871 --> 00:00:58,238
It's more like a juice than a slushie.

22
00:00:58,305 --> 00:01:01,138
At headquarters,
you can have as many as you like.

23
00:01:01,205 --> 00:01:02,371
There's a whole spread.

24
00:01:02,438 --> 00:01:04,138
SEO-JIN GETS FREE SMOOTHIES
WHENEVER HE GOES TO DALLAS

25
00:01:04,205 --> 00:01:08,305
I think it would be a good segment
since he's made it big in America.

26
00:01:08,371 --> 00:01:09,971
I love that.

27
00:01:10,038 --> 00:01:12,105
"A Look at the Life
of a Successful Businessman in America."

28
00:01:12,171 --> 00:01:13,971
The company sponsors the Dallas Cowboys.

29
00:01:14,038 --> 00:01:15,205
DALLAS COWBOYS
PARTNERSHIP STARTED IN 2021

30
00:01:15,271 --> 00:01:17,705
- They need to support the locals.
- Right.

31
00:01:17,771 --> 00:01:20,971
Look up the world's richest team.

32
00:01:21,038 --> 00:01:23,005
It's the Dallas Cowboys.

33
00:01:23,071 --> 00:01:24,805
They have the most money.

34
00:01:24,871 --> 00:01:26,605
13 BILLION-DOLLAR VALUE
A TOP-RANKED GLOBAL SPORTS TEAM

35
00:01:26,671 --> 00:01:29,838
We also need to visit a football stadium.

36
00:01:30,338 --> 00:01:32,771
- We need to go to AT&T Stadium.
- Yes.

37
00:01:32,838 --> 00:01:34,371
It's a dome.

38
00:01:34,438 --> 00:01:35,805
- What else is there?
- Dallas…

39
00:01:35,871 --> 00:01:38,438
It's the most famous steakhouse in Dallas.

40
00:01:38,505 --> 00:01:40,138
- A restaurant?
- It will come up

41
00:01:40,705 --> 00:01:42,938
if you search
"the priciest restaurant in Dallas."

42
00:01:43,005 --> 00:01:44,605
The top result is Nuri Steakhouse.

43
00:01:44,671 --> 00:01:46,138
- Dori?
- Nuri.

44
00:01:46,205 --> 00:01:47,771
It's all the rage right now.

45
00:01:48,271 --> 00:01:51,571
Did he get started here,
or did he move his company here?

46
00:01:51,638 --> 00:01:53,338
He started in New Orleans.

47
00:01:53,405 --> 00:01:56,538
He relocated the headquarters here.

48
00:01:56,605 --> 00:01:58,005
I guess he came for the same reasons.

49
00:01:58,071 --> 00:02:00,471
It's an ideal location for business
with nice weather.

50
00:02:00,538 --> 00:02:01,705
- Right?
- That's right.

51
00:02:01,771 --> 00:02:03,638
Since he started in New Orleans,

52
00:02:03,705 --> 00:02:07,105
he has ties to places
like Florida and Texas.

53
00:02:07,171 --> 00:02:09,171
MANY COMPANIES FLOCK TO TEXAS

54
00:02:09,238 --> 00:02:11,638
DUE TO LOW TAXES
AND BUSINESS-FRIENDLY REGULATIONS

55
00:02:11,705 --> 00:02:12,738
Is that the sea?

56
00:02:13,805 --> 00:02:15,505
Why would there be a sea?

57
00:02:15,571 --> 00:02:16,705
The sky looked like water.

58
00:02:16,771 --> 00:02:19,638
THE SEA ONLY DAE-JU CAN SEE

59
00:02:19,705 --> 00:02:21,938
This is a landlocked city.

60
00:02:22,005 --> 00:02:24,271
- But if you picture the sea…
- It does look like water.

61
00:02:24,338 --> 00:02:26,705
THE SEA IS 5 HOURS AWAY
DAE-JU HAS SUPERHUMAN VISION

62
00:02:26,771 --> 00:02:29,071
Dae-ju, do you know
how many people live in Texas?

63
00:02:29,838 --> 00:02:31,105
- I'm not sure.
- The total number.

64
00:02:31,171 --> 00:02:33,871
Did you know Texas is bigger than Korea?

65
00:02:33,938 --> 00:02:37,038
- You mean the land size, right?
- That's right.

66
00:02:37,105 --> 00:02:39,371
DAE-JU'S CHANCE TO REDEEM
HIS GEOGRAPHY REPUTATION

67
00:02:39,438 --> 00:02:40,405
Is it one million?

68
00:02:40,471 --> 00:02:41,805
- What?
- What?

69
00:02:42,371 --> 00:02:44,171
Is that too small or too big?

70
00:02:44,871 --> 00:02:47,005
There are ten million people in Seoul.

71
00:02:47,505 --> 00:02:48,338
That's right.

72
00:02:48,405 --> 00:02:50,705
Are there more people here than in Korea?

73
00:02:51,871 --> 00:02:53,905
- What?
- What are you saying?

74
00:02:53,971 --> 00:02:55,338
Just stop talking.

75
00:02:55,405 --> 00:02:57,371
CUTTING HIM OFF FOR HIS BENEFIT

76
00:02:57,438 --> 00:02:59,271
I'm really bad with numbers.

77
00:02:59,871 --> 00:03:01,105
Look, there's the sea.

78
00:03:01,171 --> 00:03:03,805
THE SAME SEA FROM EARLIER

79
00:03:03,871 --> 00:03:07,238
We'll go to Smoothie King
while you go for a swim, Dae-ju.

80
00:03:07,305 --> 00:03:08,305
Okay.

81
00:03:09,138 --> 00:03:11,771
Is this a business complex?

82
00:03:11,838 --> 00:03:13,005
Yes.

83
00:03:13,071 --> 00:03:15,305
TODAY'S FIRST STOP: SMOOTHIE KING

84
00:03:17,605 --> 00:03:18,538
All right.

85
00:03:18,605 --> 00:03:19,571
FEELING RIGHT AT HOME

86
00:03:19,638 --> 00:03:22,538
Let's go learn about Smoothie King.

87
00:03:29,038 --> 00:03:30,505
Should I wait in the CEO's office?

88
00:03:30,571 --> 00:03:33,038
THE CEO IS ON A BUSINESS TRIP
HE PLANS TO GO INTO AN UNOCCUPIED ROOM

89
00:03:33,105 --> 00:03:35,005
We need to film you being greeted.

90
00:03:35,071 --> 00:03:37,338
- You said they'd roll out a carpet.
- Just come with me.

91
00:03:37,405 --> 00:03:39,538
- You want me to follow?
- Yes, come on.

92
00:03:39,605 --> 00:03:41,538
This is the conference room.

93
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:44,005
Is this your company?

94
00:03:44,071 --> 00:03:47,005
I'm just guiding you.
Look at all the setup.

95
00:03:47,671 --> 00:03:49,171
There's a shop inside the store?

96
00:03:49,238 --> 00:03:50,405
INTRODUCING SOMEONE ELSE'S COMPANY

97
00:03:50,471 --> 00:03:52,571
FIDDLING

98
00:03:52,638 --> 00:03:54,638
EXPLORING SOMEONE ELSE'S MEETING ROOM

99
00:03:58,305 --> 00:03:59,905
SMOOTHIE KING MARKETING VP
TODAY'S TOUR GUIDE

100
00:04:18,038 --> 00:04:20,505
THE TOUR LED BY SHANNON BEGINS!

101
00:04:42,038 --> 00:04:43,038
What did she say?

102
00:04:43,105 --> 00:04:45,805
- They started with just straws.
- Okay.

103
00:04:46,505 --> 00:04:49,305
Now that they serve bowls,
they also need spoons.

104
00:05:02,738 --> 00:05:05,238
A NAME THAT SCREAMS SMOOTHIE COMPANY

105
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,205
This must be where they get trained.

106
00:05:26,671 --> 00:05:28,271
- He is the founder.
- Oh, I see.

107
00:05:51,738 --> 00:05:53,438
She says we should take pictures.

108
00:05:53,505 --> 00:05:54,738
SURPRISINGLY OBEDIENT

109
00:05:54,805 --> 00:05:55,938
Is this a promo shot?

110
00:05:56,971 --> 00:05:58,638
BIG GRIN

111
00:05:58,705 --> 00:06:00,338
HE WAS WAITING FOR THE OPPORTUNITY

112
00:06:00,405 --> 00:06:01,971
You look very proud.

113
00:06:04,338 --> 00:06:06,305
TAKING A COMMEMORATIVE PHOTO

114
00:06:06,371 --> 00:06:08,905
THE TOUR CONTINUES

115
00:06:26,538 --> 00:06:27,538
This is the office.

116
00:06:29,138 --> 00:06:30,205
Whose office is it?

117
00:06:30,271 --> 00:06:31,905
- Oh, is it the CEO's office?
- Yes.

118
00:06:31,971 --> 00:06:33,438
SEO-JIN'S OLD HANGOUT

119
00:06:33,505 --> 00:06:34,405
Oh, is this him?

120
00:06:35,405 --> 00:06:38,638
MERCHANDISE FROM PARTNER TEAMS

121
00:06:38,705 --> 00:06:41,338
NEW ORLEANS PELICANS,
NEW ORLEANS SAINTS, DALLAS COWBOYS

122
00:06:44,371 --> 00:06:46,538
50-YEAR-OLD MENUS ON THE WALL

123
00:06:48,471 --> 00:06:50,771
It doesn't seem like a CEO's office.

124
00:06:51,338 --> 00:06:52,805
- It's cozy, isn't it?
- Yes.

125
00:06:53,438 --> 00:06:55,138
CASUALLY REACHES

126
00:06:57,105 --> 00:06:58,438
Is that dog gum?

127
00:06:58,938 --> 00:07:00,805
No, it's chicken.

128
00:07:02,038 --> 00:07:04,271
EVEN THE CEO'S SNACKS
ARE A PART OF THE TOUR

129
00:07:04,338 --> 00:07:06,671
HEADING TO THE FINAL STOP

130
00:07:23,371 --> 00:07:24,538
THINKING

131
00:07:28,805 --> 00:07:31,538
A MOMENT LATER

132
00:07:31,605 --> 00:07:32,938
AMAZED

133
00:07:33,005 --> 00:07:34,971
A TRAY FILLED WITH SMOOTHIES

134
00:07:44,371 --> 00:07:45,671
A TASTING OF 3 SAMPLE SMOOTHIES

135
00:07:51,438 --> 00:07:53,838
I've been getting into this stuff lately.

136
00:07:54,371 --> 00:07:56,638
Since I've been exercising,

137
00:07:57,305 --> 00:08:00,638
I like to have
a high-vitamin, nutritious lunch.

138
00:08:00,705 --> 00:08:03,305
SLURP

139
00:08:03,371 --> 00:08:05,738
We don't get that many greens.

140
00:08:05,805 --> 00:08:09,238
We often end up getting a burger
or stir-fried meat.

141
00:08:09,305 --> 00:08:11,205
We need to eat things like smoothies.

142
00:08:11,271 --> 00:08:12,771
SOFT CHUCKLES

143
00:08:12,838 --> 00:08:17,238
Maybe our dear CEO
can give me one franchise in Korea?

144
00:08:17,305 --> 00:08:19,505
YUNG-SUK'S FIRST TIME TRYING SMOOTHIE KING

145
00:08:20,071 --> 00:08:22,405
You need a company for that.

146
00:08:24,371 --> 00:08:26,805
I'll make a subsidiary called
"Smoothie is Coming."

147
00:08:26,871 --> 00:08:29,838
I can't use Smoothie King
for copyright reasons.

148
00:08:29,905 --> 00:08:31,671
So we'll use Smoothie Prince.

149
00:08:31,738 --> 00:08:34,771
- Then, they can't sue--
- How about Queen?

150
00:08:34,838 --> 00:08:36,671
- Smoothie Queen?
- Yes.

151
00:08:36,738 --> 00:08:37,638
COUP OF THE FAKE ROYALS

152
00:08:37,705 --> 00:08:39,438
It seems more like a knockoff.

153
00:08:39,505 --> 00:08:40,705
Let's do our best.

154
00:08:40,771 --> 00:08:43,038
Our retirement depends on our dear CEO.

155
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:45,538
THEN SUDDENLY…

156
00:08:45,605 --> 00:08:47,838
They once sold
a Lee Seo-jin smoothie and sandwich.

157
00:08:47,905 --> 00:08:50,971
LAUNCHED BY SMOOTHIE KING 19 YEARS AGO

158
00:08:51,038 --> 00:08:53,538
You were pumped full of protein then.

159
00:08:53,605 --> 00:08:54,671
Now you're…

160
00:08:56,205 --> 00:08:57,605
Where did all my muscles go?

161
00:08:57,671 --> 00:09:00,638
THE TOUR ENDS WITH A TRIP DOWN MEMORY LANE

162
00:09:00,705 --> 00:09:06,638
- Ye-seul, we're heading there now, right?
- Yes, it's about a 25 minute-drive.

163
00:09:06,705 --> 00:09:09,071
MOVING AROUND

164
00:09:09,138 --> 00:09:12,171
SEO-JIN IS SUDDENLY BUSTLING AROUND ALONE

165
00:09:12,238 --> 00:09:14,438
- You've got it on underneath?
- I should get ready.

166
00:09:14,505 --> 00:09:16,038
You're changing?

167
00:09:16,105 --> 00:09:17,605
I'm wearing it already.

168
00:09:18,438 --> 00:09:19,371
PERFECTLY PREPARED

169
00:09:19,438 --> 00:09:21,705
You're a pro. Oh my.

170
00:09:21,771 --> 00:09:24,771
I bought this there when I went to a game.

171
00:09:25,605 --> 00:09:27,338
SEO-JIN'S T-SHIRT FORESHADOWS NEXT STOP

172
00:09:27,405 --> 00:09:29,638
You're the king
of dressing for the occasion.

173
00:09:29,705 --> 00:09:33,838
HOME OF THE DALLAS COWBOYS

174
00:09:37,338 --> 00:09:39,138
I don't get why we need to go.

175
00:09:39,205 --> 00:09:43,205
But he insisted we had to go
even though the stadium was empty.

176
00:09:44,071 --> 00:09:45,205
But seriously…

177
00:09:45,271 --> 00:09:46,905
TONGUE-TIED

178
00:09:46,971 --> 00:09:48,771
To see a stadium like this…

179
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,771
Even locals don't get this chance.

180
00:09:51,271 --> 00:09:53,038
Don't they usually have tours?

181
00:09:53,105 --> 00:09:54,871
They do.

182
00:09:54,938 --> 00:09:58,338
I don't know what the tour includes.

183
00:09:58,405 --> 00:10:00,305
- But we're getting a special tour.
- True.

184
00:10:00,371 --> 00:10:02,471
He spoke to the CEO--

185
00:10:02,538 --> 00:10:05,171
This was arranged by our dear CEO?

186
00:10:05,238 --> 00:10:07,505
Wait, he sponsors the Dallas Cowboys.

187
00:10:07,571 --> 00:10:10,271
AS WE SAW EARLIER,
SMOOTHIE KING SPONSORS MANY TEAMS

188
00:10:10,338 --> 00:10:12,071
This was set up by our dear CEO.

189
00:10:12,138 --> 00:10:14,638
I may as well take credit then
since he's my buddy.

190
00:10:14,705 --> 00:10:16,705
Oh, is that how it works?

191
00:10:17,538 --> 00:10:20,471
I hope we get to see the locker room.

192
00:10:20,971 --> 00:10:24,105
What should be
the main focus on a tour like this?

193
00:10:24,171 --> 00:10:25,471
- On this tour?
- Yes.

194
00:10:26,305 --> 00:10:28,138
Are we just taking in the vibe?

195
00:10:28,205 --> 00:10:29,438
SEO-JIN DOESN'T GET THE QUESTION

196
00:10:29,505 --> 00:10:31,505
You just…

197
00:10:31,571 --> 00:10:33,338
Everything about it is amazing.

198
00:10:34,471 --> 00:10:37,805
Is this like when I went to the ranch?

199
00:10:37,871 --> 00:10:41,138
The Dallas Cowboys' stadium
is called AT&T Stadium.

200
00:10:41,205 --> 00:10:42,471
What does AT&T stand for?

201
00:10:42,538 --> 00:10:44,638
- It's a telecommunications company.
- It's a US company.

202
00:10:44,705 --> 00:10:46,638
They're the main sponsor.

203
00:10:46,705 --> 00:10:48,138
How many seats?

204
00:10:48,205 --> 00:10:51,371
I think there are about 60,000 seats.

205
00:10:51,438 --> 00:10:53,105
That's huge.

206
00:10:53,171 --> 00:10:55,405
- It's dome-shaped.
- And it still seats 60,000?

207
00:10:55,471 --> 00:10:57,205
LARGEST DOMED STADIUM IN THE WORLD
WITH 80,000 SEATS

208
00:10:57,271 --> 00:10:58,871
For a single sport,

209
00:11:00,205 --> 00:11:03,971
American football
is number one in revenue.

210
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:05,471
Though it's just a US sport…

211
00:11:05,538 --> 00:11:08,338
Yes, even though
it's only played in the US.

212
00:11:08,405 --> 00:11:10,005
It's still number one.

213
00:11:10,738 --> 00:11:13,138
This team's always done well, right?

214
00:11:13,205 --> 00:11:16,238
Yes, but their scores aren't great.

215
00:11:17,605 --> 00:11:20,105
- So their fans have a lot of complaints.
- Right.

216
00:11:20,171 --> 00:11:23,138
But the owner doesn't care much.

217
00:11:23,205 --> 00:11:25,605
They sell a lot of goods and apparel.

218
00:11:26,105 --> 00:11:28,305
They make a lot of profit,

219
00:11:28,371 --> 00:11:30,538
so improving their performance
isn't necessary.

220
00:11:30,605 --> 00:11:33,538
The owner is Jerry Jones.

221
00:11:34,438 --> 00:11:36,338
He doesn't care about performance.

222
00:11:36,405 --> 00:11:38,538
He still makes a ton of money.

223
00:11:38,605 --> 00:11:40,005
Oh boy.

224
00:11:40,705 --> 00:11:43,005
I should have been
born into the Jones family.

225
00:11:43,505 --> 00:11:45,638
Owning an American football team…

226
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:47,038
It's your dream?

227
00:11:47,105 --> 00:11:49,605
It's the kind of thing no one can afford.

228
00:11:49,671 --> 00:11:53,071
It doesn't matter how rich you are.

229
00:11:53,138 --> 00:11:56,738
Despite all that,
I don't feel very excited.

230
00:11:56,805 --> 00:11:57,838
CLUELESS ABOUT FOOTBALL

231
00:11:58,905 --> 00:12:03,171
But didn't you watch a football film
to prepare for this tour?

232
00:12:03,238 --> 00:12:05,305
I stopped halfway. It was a bad pick.

233
00:12:06,171 --> 00:12:08,605
- What was it?
- It was a teen movie.

234
00:12:09,238 --> 00:12:11,071
- Was Denzel Washington in it?
- Yes.

235
00:12:11,638 --> 00:12:13,705
- You have to watch…
- Ryan Gosling also stars in it.

236
00:12:13,771 --> 00:12:16,605
- Does he?
- Yes, it stars a young Ryan Gosling.

237
00:12:16,671 --> 00:12:18,405
You should have watched <i>Any Given Sunday.</i>

238
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:20,605
That's what I've been told.

239
00:12:20,671 --> 00:12:22,505
Jamie Foxx plays a quarterback.

240
00:12:22,571 --> 00:12:23,905
ABOUT CONFLICT AND STRUGGLES
IN A FOOTBALL TEAM

241
00:12:23,971 --> 00:12:25,305
It stars Jamie Foxx.

242
00:12:26,038 --> 00:12:30,205
<i>Remember the Titans</i>
was about high-school American football

243
00:12:30,271 --> 00:12:32,371
during a period of racial tension.

244
00:12:32,438 --> 00:12:35,805
Didn't Sandra Bullock
also star in a football film?

245
00:12:35,871 --> 00:12:38,238
- It's about a Black player…
<i>- The Blind Side.</i>

246
00:12:39,138 --> 00:12:44,238
Did you know it resulted in a lawsuit?

247
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:46,471
- It's based on a true story.
- A white family

248
00:12:46,538 --> 00:12:51,405
adopts a Black kid who grows up
into a professional football player.

249
00:12:51,471 --> 00:12:53,471
So he became a successful player.

250
00:12:53,538 --> 00:12:56,205
But he ended up suing his family
for exploiting him.

251
00:12:56,271 --> 00:13:02,171
- But that film was moving.
- It was filmed before the lawsuit.

252
00:13:02,238 --> 00:13:03,871
So it ends on a happy note.

253
00:13:03,938 --> 00:13:07,405
Sandra Bullock won
the Best Actress award for it.

254
00:13:07,471 --> 00:13:10,738
He sued his parents,
and it was a whole big thing.

255
00:13:10,805 --> 00:13:12,005
They became estranged.

256
00:13:13,271 --> 00:13:14,605
The film is just a fantasy.

257
00:13:14,671 --> 00:13:18,371
WHILE SHOOTING THE BREEZE ABOUT MOVIES…

258
00:13:21,538 --> 00:13:22,771
- It's huge.
- Isn't it great?

259
00:13:22,838 --> 00:13:24,338
THEY ARRIVE AT THE DESTINATION

260
00:13:26,171 --> 00:13:27,438
What do you mean "shit"?

261
00:13:27,505 --> 00:13:29,771
- For American viewers…
- Who taught you English?

262
00:13:29,838 --> 00:13:32,505
- It's that big?
- It's bigger than a baseball stadium.

263
00:13:32,571 --> 00:13:34,805
Of course, they're loaded.

264
00:13:34,871 --> 00:13:37,805
- It's almost like…
- This stadium is made of money.

265
00:13:37,871 --> 00:13:40,271
It's like a landed spaceship.

266
00:13:40,938 --> 00:13:42,871
It's the shape of a football.

267
00:13:43,638 --> 00:13:45,038
I see it.

268
00:13:45,105 --> 00:13:46,705
I can't believe it's that big.

269
00:13:46,771 --> 00:13:49,805
THE DESIGNER HAS SAID
THE SHAPE WAS A COINCIDENCE

270
00:13:49,871 --> 00:13:53,305
He's wearing a short-sleeve
Dallas Cowboys T-shirt

271
00:13:53,371 --> 00:13:54,938
in this cold weather.

272
00:13:55,005 --> 00:13:56,038
STEPPING OUT WITH EXCITEMENT

273
00:14:04,371 --> 00:14:06,238
TODAY'S TOUR GUIDE IS BRIAN

274
00:14:28,705 --> 00:14:30,238
Doesn't it look amazing from here?

275
00:14:30,305 --> 00:14:31,938
- You're right.
- It does.

276
00:14:32,005 --> 00:14:33,805
This is what you call an entrance.

277
00:14:33,871 --> 00:14:35,505
Shouldn't we take a photo?

278
00:14:35,571 --> 00:14:37,071
- I'll take one for you.
- Let's do it.

279
00:14:37,138 --> 00:14:38,305
A PHOTO-WORTHY SIGHT

280
00:14:38,371 --> 00:14:40,538
- Let's stand in the center…
- Take one without me.

281
00:14:40,605 --> 00:14:41,771
It has to be all three of us.

282
00:14:41,838 --> 00:14:43,338
- Why?
- I'll take it for you.

283
00:14:43,405 --> 00:14:44,471
Stand in the middle.

284
00:14:44,538 --> 00:14:46,005
DOES IT ANYWAY

285
00:14:46,071 --> 00:14:48,171
Here we go. Three, two, one.

286
00:14:48,771 --> 00:14:50,071
AT THE STADIUM SEO-JIN'S BEEN RAVING ABOUT

287
00:14:50,738 --> 00:14:52,871
BESTIES ON CAMERA

288
00:14:52,938 --> 00:14:54,905
Seo-jin, is this ten yards?

289
00:14:54,971 --> 00:14:56,838
- No, it's smaller.
- I see.

290
00:14:56,905 --> 00:14:58,938
- Seo-jin said it was ten--
- No, this is five yards.

291
00:14:59,005 --> 00:15:00,705
Up to here is ten yards.

292
00:15:00,771 --> 00:15:02,238
This is ten yards.

293
00:15:02,305 --> 00:15:03,571
It's hard to get past, right?

294
00:15:03,638 --> 00:15:05,438
It takes at least four tries.

295
00:15:05,505 --> 00:15:07,538
- You need four tries?
- Yes.

296
00:15:07,605 --> 00:15:09,305
- You start here.
- Okay.

297
00:15:09,371 --> 00:15:13,205
The quarterback stands here with the ball.

298
00:15:13,271 --> 00:15:15,271
They need to get all the way across.

299
00:15:28,471 --> 00:15:29,938
So this is 50 yards.

300
00:15:34,971 --> 00:15:36,005
EXCITED

301
00:15:36,071 --> 00:15:39,371
I think he's taking us
to see the actual stadium.

302
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,871
- Now you're a football fan?
- I think we get to…

303
00:15:41,938 --> 00:15:43,305
FINALLY ENTERING THE STADIUM

304
00:15:48,771 --> 00:15:50,605
BRIAN KNOWS HOW TO PLAY HARD TO GET

305
00:15:53,338 --> 00:15:54,638
I got chills.

306
00:15:54,705 --> 00:15:56,371
I got goosebumps.

307
00:15:57,805 --> 00:15:59,071
It's so awesome.

308
00:15:59,138 --> 00:16:00,938
FIRST-TIME VISITORS LEFT SPEECHLESS

309
00:16:01,005 --> 00:16:02,538
I told you so.

310
00:16:02,605 --> 00:16:04,271
I only speak facts.

311
00:16:04,338 --> 00:16:07,738
- Unbelievable.
- You can see it cost a fortune.

312
00:16:07,805 --> 00:16:09,038
IT'S JUST AS SEO-JIN DESCRIBED

313
00:16:09,571 --> 00:16:10,905
It's so impressive.

314
00:16:10,971 --> 00:16:13,571
EVEN AN EMPTY STADIUM IS WORTH A VISIT

315
00:16:35,438 --> 00:16:38,538
It's so awesome.
It's different seeing it in person.

316
00:16:38,605 --> 00:16:40,171
HIS DIMPLES DEEPEN WITH PRIDE

317
00:17:34,071 --> 00:17:36,305
They take all that out and put down grass.

318
00:17:36,371 --> 00:17:38,405
Then they take all the grass out
and put down dirt.

319
00:17:38,471 --> 00:17:41,071
After the rodeo, they take the dirt out.

320
00:17:41,138 --> 00:17:43,538
I want to work in this industry.

321
00:17:43,605 --> 00:17:44,605
What?

322
00:17:44,671 --> 00:17:47,071
You said you weren't excited.
What changed?

323
00:17:47,138 --> 00:17:48,805
It's so awesome.

324
00:17:49,405 --> 00:17:51,505
It's so high-class.

325
00:17:51,571 --> 00:17:52,638
A RAPID CHANGE OF STANCE

326
00:18:03,471 --> 00:18:05,638
Oh, F stands for "field."

327
00:18:06,371 --> 00:18:08,205
- The floor names…
- Yes.

328
00:18:10,238 --> 00:18:11,705
ELEVATOR DING

329
00:18:14,938 --> 00:18:18,205
You said you didn't care,
but you seem the most excited.

330
00:18:18,905 --> 00:18:20,571
- As soon as the doors open…
- I'll run out.

331
00:18:20,638 --> 00:18:22,805
- Go and do a touchdown.
- I'll do it.

332
00:18:23,838 --> 00:18:26,705
STEPS OUT CAUTIOUSLY

333
00:18:26,771 --> 00:18:28,605
There's the locker room.

334
00:18:28,671 --> 00:18:30,605
SEO-JIN'S MIND IS ALL ABOUT THE LOCKER

335
00:18:30,671 --> 00:18:34,171
The players make an impression
when they enter.

336
00:18:34,938 --> 00:18:38,071
They have a warrior-like energy.

337
00:18:43,738 --> 00:18:46,738
WHAT'S WAITING AT THE END OF THE CORRIDOR?

338
00:18:48,271 --> 00:18:51,538
GREEN GLOW THAT HEIGHTENS ANTICIPATION

339
00:18:53,971 --> 00:18:57,138
WALK STRAIGHT DOWN THE PATH

340
00:18:58,071 --> 00:19:00,338
They do events here.

341
00:19:01,938 --> 00:19:04,405
TO FIND A WIDE-OPEN FIELD

342
00:19:05,871 --> 00:19:08,305
This is real. It's real grass.

343
00:19:08,371 --> 00:19:12,905
I looked up some clips online
as research for this tour.

344
00:19:12,971 --> 00:19:14,171
The stadium looked small.

345
00:19:14,238 --> 00:19:15,705
It just looks small

346
00:19:15,771 --> 00:19:17,605
- because the players are so big.
- That must be it.

347
00:19:17,671 --> 00:19:20,238
- They make the field look packed.
- Right.

348
00:19:20,305 --> 00:19:22,105
It is huge.

349
00:19:22,171 --> 00:19:24,171
It's the size of a soccer field.

350
00:19:25,505 --> 00:19:27,438
They won the world championship…

351
00:19:27,505 --> 00:19:28,638
Take a photo of me.

352
00:19:28,705 --> 00:19:29,905
They won the world championship.

353
00:19:29,971 --> 00:19:31,771
- Five times?
- No, more than that.

354
00:19:31,838 --> 00:19:33,038
SUPER BOWL VICTORY BANNERS

355
00:19:33,105 --> 00:19:34,638
They last won in 1995.

356
00:19:34,705 --> 00:19:37,371
TWO FOCUSED ENTHUSIASTS AND…

357
00:19:37,438 --> 00:19:38,938
You're right.

358
00:19:39,005 --> 00:19:41,371
ONE EXCITED MUGGLE

359
00:19:41,438 --> 00:19:43,071
You look like a thief on the run!

360
00:19:43,571 --> 00:19:45,371
They won five times, right?

361
00:19:45,438 --> 00:19:47,405
It was when they had Troy Aikman.

362
00:19:47,938 --> 00:19:48,771
That's right.

363
00:19:49,738 --> 00:19:51,038
They haven't won it since.

364
00:19:51,105 --> 00:19:52,538
- It's been a long time.
- It has.

365
00:19:52,605 --> 00:19:55,105
That's why their fans are so mad.

366
00:19:57,038 --> 00:20:01,905
NAMES AROUND THE STADIUM

367
00:20:15,838 --> 00:20:18,038
Troy Aikman, Emmitt Smith, Michael Irvin.

368
00:20:18,105 --> 00:20:20,305
- Michael Irvin.
- They're from the same era.

369
00:20:21,471 --> 00:20:23,071
- They played together.
- It's all one era.

370
00:20:23,138 --> 00:20:25,638
That's why they won
in 1992, 1993, and 1995.

371
00:20:25,705 --> 00:20:28,238
- They won consecutively.
- Three times.

372
00:20:28,305 --> 00:20:30,205
- It was a golden era.
- I see.

373
00:20:30,271 --> 00:20:34,238
- Troy Aikman was the quarterback.
- Okay.

374
00:20:34,305 --> 00:20:36,971
- Emmitt Smith ran with the ball.
- Oh, I see.

375
00:20:37,471 --> 00:20:39,238
They won the championship
together three times.

376
00:20:39,305 --> 00:20:43,071
- This trio led the team to victory.
- They sure did.

377
00:20:43,138 --> 00:20:44,105
So this is the place.

378
00:20:44,171 --> 00:20:45,505
ONTO THE NEXT PART OF THE TOUR

379
00:20:45,571 --> 00:20:47,338
The players come in from that side.

380
00:20:47,405 --> 00:20:49,138
Fans gather here to watch.

381
00:20:49,205 --> 00:20:51,905
The tickets must be really pricey.

382
00:21:11,138 --> 00:21:13,171
- They all stand here like this.
- Yeah.

383
00:21:13,238 --> 00:21:15,038
EXCITED JUST THINKING ABOUT IT

384
00:21:15,105 --> 00:21:16,705
AND FINALLY…

385
00:21:16,771 --> 00:21:17,938
The VIP cars come in this way.

386
00:21:19,505 --> 00:21:21,171
It's the locker room.

387
00:21:31,905 --> 00:21:36,671
A PLACE FOR THE PLAYERS TO REST
AND PREPARE FOR THE MATCH

388
00:21:36,738 --> 00:21:40,605
EQUIPPED WITH PERSONAL LOCKERS
AND SHOWER FACILITIES

389
00:21:42,471 --> 00:21:43,471
It's this way.

390
00:21:43,538 --> 00:21:44,371
Okay.

391
00:21:55,038 --> 00:21:58,171
SEO-JIN SITS ON THE OFFENSE SIDE

392
00:21:58,238 --> 00:22:01,105
Sit by a star player's locker.
Who did you choose?

393
00:22:01,171 --> 00:22:03,571
- This is CeeDee Lamb's.
- Do you want a picture?

394
00:22:03,638 --> 00:22:06,205
- Do you want one? You need to ask for it.
- Okay.

395
00:22:06,271 --> 00:22:07,871
- Do you want one? He wants one.
- Yes.

396
00:22:07,938 --> 00:22:09,105
FORCED TO MAKE A PHOTO REQUEST

397
00:22:09,171 --> 00:22:10,605
Here we go. Three, two, one.

398
00:22:10,671 --> 00:22:12,938
IT WAS A PLEASURE, CEEDEE LAMB

399
00:22:13,605 --> 00:22:16,071
SEO-JIN'S SECOND PHOTO BY REQUEST

400
00:22:16,138 --> 00:22:18,005
You're gleaming.

401
00:22:18,071 --> 00:22:19,571
You look thrilled.

402
00:22:22,205 --> 00:22:23,138
SEO-JIN'S DREAM IS FULFILLED

403
00:22:23,205 --> 00:22:25,405
In all my time working with Seo-jin,

404
00:22:25,471 --> 00:22:27,338
I've never seen him smile like this.

405
00:22:27,405 --> 00:22:29,371
- What do you mean?
- It's the first time.

406
00:22:30,105 --> 00:22:32,505
- This is a really rare opportunity.
- I should have brought you sooner

407
00:22:32,571 --> 00:22:34,438
instead of dragging you to the ranch.

408
00:22:35,038 --> 00:22:36,571
My goodness.

409
00:22:36,638 --> 00:22:38,238
We need to visit the Pro Shop.

410
00:22:38,305 --> 00:22:40,371
Yes, that's the last stop of the tour.

411
00:22:40,871 --> 00:22:43,838
Is it time for the cash grab?

412
00:22:43,905 --> 00:22:44,838
A FEW MINUTES LATER

413
00:22:44,905 --> 00:22:48,238
BUYING IN BULK

414
00:22:48,305 --> 00:22:53,305
It always ends with buying clothes.

415
00:22:53,371 --> 00:22:54,371
CAPITALISM WINS AGAIN

416
00:22:54,438 --> 00:22:56,038
You don't need more clothes, do you?

417
00:22:56,105 --> 00:22:57,705
For tomorrow's itinerary…

418
00:22:57,771 --> 00:22:59,905
- NASA.
- NASA clothing?

419
00:22:59,971 --> 00:23:03,371
We're going to wear space suits
for tomorrow's tour.

420
00:23:09,338 --> 00:23:12,005
We might need another suitcase.

421
00:23:12,071 --> 00:23:14,938
Can you imagine if we came in our boots?

422
00:23:15,571 --> 00:23:17,505
We would've had such sore heels.

423
00:23:17,571 --> 00:23:19,371
Can you imagine?

424
00:23:19,438 --> 00:23:22,705
I'm going to wear them when we go to Nuri.

425
00:23:23,238 --> 00:23:25,438
I might also wear my hat.

426
00:23:25,505 --> 00:23:28,271
You need to wear a cowboy hat
to a steakhouse.

427
00:23:28,338 --> 00:23:31,071
Do they have
anything to do with a steakhouse?

428
00:23:31,138 --> 00:23:32,205
It's got that vibe.

429
00:23:32,271 --> 00:23:35,571
DINNER AFTER A QUICK REFRESH

430
00:23:37,171 --> 00:23:40,371
What's the name
of the place we're going to?

431
00:23:40,438 --> 00:23:41,905
It's Nuri.

432
00:23:41,971 --> 00:23:43,771
- It's Nuri Steakhouse, right?
- Yes.

433
00:23:43,838 --> 00:23:46,805
It serves food with a Korean fusion twist,

434
00:23:46,871 --> 00:23:52,105
and it's currently the most popular
high-end restaurant in Dallas.

435
00:23:52,171 --> 00:23:54,971
It's owned by a very close friend of mine.

436
00:23:55,038 --> 00:23:58,871
Is the main aim of the menu
to promote Korean food?

437
00:23:58,938 --> 00:24:01,371
It's just food he likes to eat.

438
00:24:01,438 --> 00:24:04,371
That friend of mine
is in a league of his own.

439
00:24:04,905 --> 00:24:06,405
As soon as you go in,

440
00:24:06,471 --> 00:24:08,971
- there's a place for drinks.
- Yes, there's a bar.

441
00:24:09,038 --> 00:24:10,938
People were drinking at the bar,
all dressed up.

442
00:24:11,005 --> 00:24:11,838
Already?

443
00:24:11,905 --> 00:24:15,405
I felt a bit daunted
as soon as we walked in.

444
00:24:17,138 --> 00:24:21,005
Ye-seul isn't easily intimidated,
so that says a lot.

445
00:24:21,071 --> 00:24:24,338
I might throw up today.

446
00:24:24,405 --> 00:24:26,471
If Ye-seul felt daunted, I'm screwed.

447
00:24:26,538 --> 00:24:28,105
YE-SEUL IS 5 TIMES BRAVER THAN YUNG-SUK

448
00:24:28,171 --> 00:24:33,438
We wanted to dress up for the occasion,
so we shopped at Ralph Lauren yesterday.

449
00:24:35,238 --> 00:24:37,938
Are you embarrassed
to take me to a steakhouse?

450
00:24:38,005 --> 00:24:38,905
Isn't this better?

451
00:24:38,971 --> 00:24:40,871
I think this will look better.

452
00:24:40,938 --> 00:24:43,338
- I think that looks good.
- Really?

453
00:24:43,405 --> 00:24:44,905
Do you own white pants?

454
00:24:44,971 --> 00:24:46,071
We're shopping at Ralph Lauren.

455
00:24:46,138 --> 00:24:47,238
OUTFIT TO WEAR TO THE RESTAURANT

456
00:24:47,305 --> 00:24:48,471
I need an Instagram shot.

457
00:24:49,038 --> 00:24:51,538
You're even wearing the boots.

458
00:24:51,605 --> 00:24:53,671
No wonder you made me dress up.

459
00:24:53,738 --> 00:24:55,271
OLD-MONEY LOOK, OLD LOOK

460
00:24:55,838 --> 00:24:59,171
This is a good place
for young people to take a stroll

461
00:24:59,238 --> 00:25:00,938
and walk their dogs.

462
00:25:01,005 --> 00:25:04,405
It's a great place to live and work.

463
00:25:04,471 --> 00:25:05,538
CLEAN AND SCENIC DALLAS

464
00:25:05,605 --> 00:25:08,605
It feels very clean and safe.

465
00:25:08,671 --> 00:25:10,805
Aren't those buildings impressive?

466
00:25:10,871 --> 00:25:12,238
- They are.
- Right?

467
00:25:12,305 --> 00:25:15,305
Are they old or just classically designed?

468
00:25:15,371 --> 00:25:16,371
It's stunning.

469
00:25:16,438 --> 00:25:20,171
I bet people in Dallas
want to live in this neighborhood.

470
00:25:21,805 --> 00:25:24,571
A few days ago, I was shooting shotguns,
and now I'm here.

471
00:25:24,638 --> 00:25:25,805
It feels so weird.

472
00:25:25,871 --> 00:25:27,538
DOWNTOWN DALLAS
WITH A DIFFERENT CHARM FROM FORT WORTH

473
00:25:27,605 --> 00:25:28,771
Look, it's a tram.

474
00:25:30,338 --> 00:25:31,571
- Is this the place?
- Yes.

475
00:25:31,638 --> 00:25:32,738
THEY ARRIVED AS THEY EXPLORED THE CITY

476
00:25:32,805 --> 00:25:36,071
We've arrived at the place
that made Ye-seul feel intimidated.

477
00:25:36,138 --> 00:25:37,805
It's Nuri Steakhouse.

478
00:25:38,471 --> 00:25:39,705
We're here at last.

479
00:25:41,971 --> 00:25:43,671
It says Nuri in Korean.

480
00:25:43,738 --> 00:25:45,938
KOREAN-FUSION STEAKHOUSE
POPULAR WITH CELEBRITIES

481
00:25:46,005 --> 00:25:47,971
ENTERING

482
00:25:48,038 --> 00:25:49,371
It's packed.

483
00:25:50,205 --> 00:25:52,205
It has a great vibe.

484
00:25:52,271 --> 00:25:54,005
It's not your typical steakhouse.

485
00:25:54,071 --> 00:25:56,638
- I love the ambiance here.
- Same.

486
00:25:56,705 --> 00:25:59,705
- It's like…
- It's so sophisticated.

487
00:25:59,771 --> 00:26:01,071
IT IS DALLAS'S FINEST RESTAURANT

488
00:26:01,138 --> 00:26:03,738
AN EXCLUSIVE WINE ROOM

489
00:26:03,805 --> 00:26:07,871
A COLLECTION CHOSEN BY A MASTER SOMMELIER

490
00:26:07,938 --> 00:26:10,705
MEANWHILE IN THE HEAT-FILLED KITCHEN

491
00:26:11,405 --> 00:26:14,771
THE CHEFS COOK TRADITIONAL STEAKS

492
00:26:14,838 --> 00:26:20,038
AND PREPARE FUSION KOREAN DISHES

493
00:26:20,105 --> 00:26:21,171
We're at Nuri Steakhouse.

494
00:26:21,238 --> 00:26:22,238
GETTING SETTLED IN

495
00:26:22,305 --> 00:26:25,238
It's run by a close friend of ours.

496
00:26:25,871 --> 00:26:28,205
STUDYING THE MENU

497
00:26:28,771 --> 00:26:30,038
This is hard.

498
00:26:30,105 --> 00:26:31,438
I'm lost.

499
00:26:31,505 --> 00:26:32,438
Where do we start?

500
00:26:32,505 --> 00:26:33,771
ALL DRESSED UP,
BUT NOT QUITE CONFIDENT YET

501
00:26:34,505 --> 00:26:35,438
Oh, hello.

502
00:26:35,505 --> 00:26:38,871
Everyone, this is our chef.

503
00:26:38,938 --> 00:26:40,171
Hello, it's nice to meet you.

504
00:26:40,238 --> 00:26:42,071
I always wanted to meet you.

505
00:26:42,138 --> 00:26:42,971
I'm honored.

506
00:26:43,038 --> 00:26:44,105
MICHELIN STAR CHEF
NURI CULINARY DIRECTOR

507
00:26:44,171 --> 00:26:48,538
- We've prepared a special course for you.
- Okay, great.

508
00:26:48,605 --> 00:26:50,938
TODAY'S MENU: CHEF'S SPECIAL

509
00:26:53,705 --> 00:26:55,238
This place is great, Seo-jin.

510
00:26:55,305 --> 00:26:57,638
The name of this place is even Nuri.

511
00:26:57,705 --> 00:27:02,371
The finest steakhouse in Texas
is called Nuri.

512
00:27:02,971 --> 00:27:04,238
Look at this.

513
00:27:04,938 --> 00:27:06,405
FIRST COURSE SERVED

514
00:27:06,471 --> 00:27:07,905
They're oysters.

515
00:27:08,471 --> 00:27:09,871
GIANT SEAFOOD TOWER

516
00:27:09,938 --> 00:27:11,338
It's lobster.

517
00:27:11,405 --> 00:27:12,471
I can't believe it!

518
00:27:20,538 --> 00:27:23,038
A TREAT FOR THE EYES AND THE PALATE

519
00:27:23,105 --> 00:27:24,905
SEO-JIN STARTS WITH THE OYSTER

520
00:27:26,871 --> 00:27:29,005
SLURP

521
00:27:31,705 --> 00:27:34,571
- The oysters are really tasty.
- They are.

522
00:27:34,638 --> 00:27:36,605
These baby oysters are great.

523
00:27:36,671 --> 00:27:39,571
It's very different from Korean oysters.

524
00:27:40,305 --> 00:27:41,705
- Ye-seul.
- Yes?

525
00:27:41,771 --> 00:27:43,738
- Scoop up more caviar.
- More?

526
00:27:43,805 --> 00:27:45,871
Don't be shy. You can have it all.

527
00:27:45,938 --> 00:27:48,171
CAVIAR: THE PINNACLE OF LUXURY

528
00:27:48,238 --> 00:27:49,971
Ye-seul knows how to eat in style.

529
00:27:50,038 --> 00:27:52,871
- Right? She knows.
- This isn't her first time.

530
00:27:53,671 --> 00:27:54,505
Try this.

531
00:27:54,571 --> 00:27:55,538
BUSY FEEDING OTHERS

532
00:27:55,605 --> 00:27:57,938
Put all of this in there.

533
00:27:58,005 --> 00:27:58,905
Try it.

534
00:27:59,971 --> 00:28:00,971
Try the lobster.

535
00:28:01,038 --> 00:28:02,138
CONTINUES TO TAKE CARE OF OTHERS

536
00:28:02,205 --> 00:28:04,271
Have you tried it? Try it.

537
00:28:04,338 --> 00:28:06,605
- Have you tried the shrimp, Ye-seul?
- I did.

538
00:28:06,671 --> 00:28:07,971
- What about you, Yu-jin?
- I did.

539
00:28:08,038 --> 00:28:09,005
Try it.

540
00:28:09,971 --> 00:28:10,805
Try this.

541
00:28:10,871 --> 00:28:12,438
LIKE AN OLD MAN FEEDING HIS GRANDSON

542
00:28:12,505 --> 00:28:14,938
Try the octopus.

543
00:28:15,005 --> 00:28:16,838
It's so tender.

544
00:28:16,905 --> 00:28:18,671
I've never had an octopus this tender.

545
00:28:18,738 --> 00:28:20,005
SEO-JIN'S SECOND FAVORITE
SOUS VIDE OCTOPUS

546
00:28:20,071 --> 00:28:21,105
Have it in one bite.

547
00:28:21,171 --> 00:28:22,205
HESITANT

548
00:28:22,271 --> 00:28:23,905
As if.

549
00:28:23,971 --> 00:28:25,005
Go on. Try it.

550
00:28:25,605 --> 00:28:27,471
It's the most tender I've ever had.

551
00:28:30,571 --> 00:28:31,871
LOOKS AWAY

552
00:28:31,938 --> 00:28:33,571
YUNG-SUK'S SHOW OF APPROVAL

553
00:28:33,638 --> 00:28:35,005
I could eat this in my sleep.

554
00:28:39,438 --> 00:28:40,538
STEAK PLATTER

555
00:28:40,605 --> 00:28:42,505
INCLUDES TOMAHAWK, NEW YORK STRIP,

556
00:28:42,571 --> 00:28:44,405
PORTER HOUSE, LAMB RIB,
AND BEEF BONE MARROW

557
00:28:44,471 --> 00:28:45,638
You can do that with a candle?

558
00:28:45,705 --> 00:28:47,905
CANDLE MADE OF WAGYU FAT
FOR THE FINISHING TOUCH

559
00:28:47,971 --> 00:28:49,171
This is amazing.

560
00:28:50,005 --> 00:28:51,738
DIGS STRAIGHT IN

561
00:28:51,805 --> 00:28:53,171
This meat is so good.

562
00:28:54,271 --> 00:28:56,271
SEO-JIN TRIES IT WITH SAUCE

563
00:28:56,338 --> 00:28:57,538
MUNCH

564
00:28:57,605 --> 00:28:59,038
This meat is amazing.

565
00:29:01,038 --> 00:29:02,338
LAYS FORK DOWN

566
00:29:03,405 --> 00:29:05,505
Woo-jung, I'm done.

567
00:29:05,571 --> 00:29:06,971
SO FULL

568
00:29:07,038 --> 00:29:08,638
I can't eat anymore.

569
00:29:09,138 --> 00:29:11,838
REACHED HIS LIMIT
WITH TEXAS-SIZED PORTIONS

570
00:29:11,905 --> 00:29:13,571
But there's also dessert.

571
00:29:13,638 --> 00:29:15,638
Isn't it ice cream?

572
00:29:16,838 --> 00:29:18,005
I don't know.

573
00:29:18,905 --> 00:29:21,871
Your eyes look drowsy.

574
00:29:21,938 --> 00:29:22,905
Are you okay?

575
00:29:22,971 --> 00:29:25,305
American food wears you out after a while.

576
00:29:25,371 --> 00:29:27,571
My biological clock's confused.

577
00:29:27,638 --> 00:29:31,671
It keeps asking me,
"Why are you still eating?"

578
00:29:32,438 --> 00:29:35,105
American portions are huge.

579
00:29:35,171 --> 00:29:38,171
They order big servings
and take the leftovers home.

580
00:29:38,838 --> 00:29:39,671
That's very common.

581
00:29:39,738 --> 00:29:41,305
WITH LARGE PORTIONS
IT'S COMMON TO TAKE LEFTOVERS HOME

582
00:29:41,371 --> 00:29:43,038
But they're bursting with energy.

583
00:29:43,105 --> 00:29:45,338
- It's just us.
- Where?

584
00:29:45,405 --> 00:29:46,638
They're having a party.

585
00:29:46,705 --> 00:29:48,271
Ju-yeong is very bubbly.

586
00:29:48,338 --> 00:29:49,171
CREW MEMBERS BURSTING WITH ENERGY

587
00:29:49,238 --> 00:29:50,438
She's leading the conversation.

588
00:29:50,505 --> 00:29:51,505
It's like a wrap party.

589
00:29:51,571 --> 00:29:53,838
They're built for fine dining.

590
00:29:53,905 --> 00:29:54,905
I guess so.

591
00:29:55,838 --> 00:29:58,071
We're the only ones who are like this.

592
00:29:58,138 --> 00:30:00,738
We're not used to this culture.

593
00:30:00,805 --> 00:30:02,671
We didn't have this growing up.

594
00:30:03,171 --> 00:30:05,838
But you used to eat roast meat.

595
00:30:05,905 --> 00:30:07,105
We roasted it at home.

596
00:30:07,171 --> 00:30:09,105
Your family was well-off.

597
00:30:09,171 --> 00:30:11,638
BACK TO BICKERING AS USUAL

598
00:30:12,338 --> 00:30:16,271
What do the locals talk about
over a meal like this?

599
00:30:16,338 --> 00:30:18,838
They're all chatting away.

600
00:30:18,905 --> 00:30:20,805
How can I describe it?

601
00:30:20,871 --> 00:30:22,705
It's just light conversation.

602
00:30:23,205 --> 00:30:24,705
They don't go too deep.

603
00:30:25,271 --> 00:30:27,338
Is it just trivial stuff?

604
00:30:27,405 --> 00:30:29,838
It could be about anything.

605
00:30:29,905 --> 00:30:31,805
If we do a press event,

606
00:30:31,871 --> 00:30:36,605
can we dress up as cowboys
and use a lasso on stage?

607
00:30:37,305 --> 00:30:39,471
I'll hold it from behind.

608
00:30:40,071 --> 00:30:41,505
Let's just do this.

609
00:30:41,571 --> 00:30:43,471
- You wear the space suit.
- Okay.

610
00:30:43,538 --> 00:30:44,771
You wear the cowboy outfit.

611
00:30:44,838 --> 00:30:46,138
I'll wear Ralph Lauren.

612
00:30:46,205 --> 00:30:48,405
- Come on.
- Come on.

613
00:30:48,971 --> 00:30:50,505
Don't be ridiculous.

614
00:30:50,571 --> 00:30:53,338
It's perfect.
We each wear a different outfit.

615
00:30:53,405 --> 00:30:56,405
Let's do this.
Whoever wins a shooting match…

616
00:30:57,405 --> 00:30:59,305
Whoever wins gets to decide.

617
00:30:59,371 --> 00:31:00,905
Salute!

618
00:31:00,971 --> 00:31:03,305
You should go up against a Navy SEAL.

619
00:31:03,805 --> 00:31:05,205
You might win.

620
00:31:06,305 --> 00:31:10,171
The film <i>G.I. Jane</i>
is about Navy SEAL training.

621
00:31:10,238 --> 00:31:13,371
- I see.
- It stars Demi Moore, right?

622
00:31:13,438 --> 00:31:15,071
So much of our trivia is from films.

623
00:31:15,138 --> 00:31:17,638
All the stuff we know
about the Navy and the NYPD

624
00:31:17,705 --> 00:31:21,038
comes from films we watched
when we were younger.

625
00:31:21,105 --> 00:31:22,938
That's the power of Hollywood.

626
00:31:23,638 --> 00:31:27,705
I don't mean in terms of money
but the stuff under the surface.

627
00:31:27,771 --> 00:31:32,605
Its cultural influence
is really beyond what we imagine.

628
00:31:32,671 --> 00:31:35,771
DESSERT HAS ARRIVED

629
00:31:35,838 --> 00:31:36,738
I suddenly feel awake.

630
00:31:37,938 --> 00:31:40,105
It's the kind of dessert women like.

631
00:31:40,171 --> 00:31:41,271
It's so good.

632
00:31:43,505 --> 00:31:45,005
He dropped the cake.

633
00:31:49,105 --> 00:31:49,938
You got lucky.

634
00:31:50,005 --> 00:31:51,171
USING HIS HANDS

635
00:31:51,238 --> 00:31:52,605
I retrieved it.

636
00:31:52,671 --> 00:31:55,405
JUST LOOKS AWAY

637
00:31:55,471 --> 00:31:59,071
I think it's worth experiencing
something like this

638
00:31:59,571 --> 00:32:02,171
at least once in your life.

639
00:32:02,238 --> 00:32:03,238
I'm so full.

640
00:32:03,305 --> 00:32:04,605
HAVING ENJOYED A GOOD MEAL,
TO BE CONTINUED

641
00:32:04,671 --> 00:32:06,071
I need to get up and move.

642
00:32:51,838 --> 00:32:56,838
Subtitle translation by: Hannah Og Nam
